The paper discusses the elicitation of utilities, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of minimax regret criterion and optimization techniques suggests a focus on decision making and optimization, which are also relevant to data science (cs.DS) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the application of preference-based constrained configuration optimization and search in multiattribute product databases suggests a potential focus on computational engineering (cs.CE).
